    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>Clinton Makes His Last Hurrah</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>George Samuels letter, commenting on August 15 article, says Pres Clinton's address at Democratic National Convention in Los Angeles underscores why Democrats deserve to maintain presidency in November</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''Clinton, Opening Convention, Says Gore Will Protect Legacy'' (front page, Aug. 15):</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''Clinton, Opening Convention, Says Gore Will Protect Legacy'' (front page, Aug. 15):</p>
        <p>President Clinton's speech at the Democratic National Convention underscores why the Democrats deserve to maintain the presidency this coming November: they have a tangible record. They have a record of hard facts and figures on what they have done for Americans and how we have become a better place.</p>
        <p>More people are working, and more people are doing better. Republicans need to start talking about what they've done to make this country a better place for all Americans. As of now, all they have to show is a failed legacy of trickle-down economics and an exasperated call for bringing morality back to the Oval Office -- and that's not much.</p>
        <p>GEORGE SAMUELS  Cambridge, Mass., Aug. 15, 2000</p>
      </block>
